doc.previous: The Canberra class of landing helicopter docks, based on the Spanish vessel Juan Carlos I, is composed of two ships one of which has just entered service. The class is being built by Navantia and BAE Systems Australia; and HMAS Canberra is the largest ship ever built for the Royal Australian Navy.[39] Canberra underwent sea trials in late 2013 and has been commissioned in 2014, while HMAS Adelaide is expected to enter service in 2016. The Australian version retains the ski-ramp from the Juan Carlos I design, although the RAN has not acquired carrier based fixed-wing aircraft.
